node.text: Faye’s room is finished, and we’re loving it! #ad We put together this little video showing how the room came together over time and also how I used @Honey to shop a mix of save-splurge, high-low pieces. With one click, Honey automatically applied discounts to our cart so we were able to save money on almost every piece — maximizing our budget and even allowing for a few bonus buys! Manually searching for promo codes is a thing of the past—Honey is free to install and just takes two clicks. Go to joinhoney.com/clj before doing any more online shopping. 🖤 #honeyapp #honey #fayesroom

node.text: Salad doesn’t always feel “wintery” to me, but once the holidays pass and my body can’t take anymore sugar, I just need something fresh. But I also like to eat seasonally, when I can. Full recipe at chrislovesjulia.com. #chriscooks #salad #dairyfree #grainfree #glutenfree #healthyeating

node.text: This is a really important week of #cljsummerschool. Week 3 of how to fall in love with your home in 30 days is about getting out of your comfort zone. This is going to look different for everyone but I promise getting out of your comfort zone can push you closer to building a unique and inseparable love for your home. It’s going to require some courage and looking inward and a lot of fun. Head to chrislovesjulia.com (link in profile) for more!

node.text: These week in #cljsummerschool, we have been talking all about how rituals can deepen your love for wherever you live. Today, I’m handing my teacher torch over today to a couple of real experts who have been loving on their Boston Queen Anne Victorian for over three years and creating meaningful routines along the way to make it feel like home faster. Their historic home is a mecca of DIY passion projects, full of so much heart, and meaningful moments. @renovationhusbands are here!!!! (In your best Oprah voice, please!) and they are spilling all about home and rituals today on chrislovesjulia.com! Link in profile!

node.text: Homesickness hit today. We left #cljmoderncottage 26 days ago and I guess that was the limit on how much fun we could have in transition before we felt that tinge in our hearts and guts and were ready to be back to our old life and settled. I got a lot of questions about how I'm handling that--especially with our three girls--our youngest is really missing "her house", and I guess I'm not stopping it. We're looking at photos and remembering things and talking about everything and crying and then when we get that all out, we drive to our new house from the hotel down the street and get so excited for our future there. It feels real. And happy. And sad. But mostly, I think we'll all feel a lot better when we get to sleep in our own beds. A cure for just about everything, I've learned. 🖤 #cljmoderncolonial

node.text:
I do my makeup nearly every day because it really gives me a pep in my step and it’s something I enjoy. Making space for a vanity in our primary closet allowed me to elevate that routine into a ritual. I sat down in that comfy chair and caught up on Marco Polo messages with friends while I did my makeup. 

So, this week, as we talk about creating rituals in our homes for #cljsummerschool, before you try to re-invent the wheel, think about how you can elevate or dedicate space or routines you already have into rituals for self and home care. There's a worksheet to fill out in today's post on chrislovesjulia.com to help you think more about this because what's summer school without worksheets? 🤓 link in profile!

node.text: I've never showed this angle of our new living room--let's call it the before. The Juliette balcony in the living room had me a little 🧐 the first time we walked through the house. We even considered walling it in! But I knew our girls would love it. I knew there would be so many plays and fashion shows and memories right there in that cut out over looking the living room. I still have some plans for the area but I'm more excited than ever. #cljmoderncolonial
